<%#
  Top Up Wallet — the FIRST funds modal a logged-in player sees when they try
  to enter a contest and lack funds. This trigger (the board's no_tokens entry
  blocker) fires ONLY for managed-wallet (web2) players, and a managed entry is
  paid by CONSUMING AN ENTRY TOKEN, not USDC. So this modal is TOKEN-FIRST: the
  primary CTA buys entry tokens (opens the existing pack picker, the tokens-
  picker step of the auth wizard), and adding USDC is demoted to the quiet
  "More ways to add funds" link into the Add Funds hub (onramp-hub), where the
  Coinbase / PayPal / Venmo rails live as the fallback.

  One modal id ('wallet-topup'); no internal step machine. Opened by the board's
  funds-needed entry blocker (selectionBoard#showWalletTopup) via
  $store.modals.open('wallet-topup', {}) on a cold board, or swap() mid-flow.

  The token count comes from $store.session.tokensAvailable (the layout session
  payload, coerced to a number, 0 when cold), so a managed player sees exactly
  why they are blocked ("Entry tokens: 0") and the primary CTA resolves it.

  Modeled on modals/_onramp_hub + _wallet_deposit. CRITICAL: rendered inside a
  host template x-if, so a SINGLE root element. x-data is a double-quoted
  attribute, so single-quote everything inside the Alpine expressions (the get
  props() accessor, the token-count x-text, the @click swaps).
%>
<div x-data="{ get props() { return ($store.modals.current() || {}).props || {} } }"
     class="relative">

  <%# Top-right close. Backdrop close still works too. %>
  <button @click="$store.modals.close()"
          class="absolute top-0 right-0 -mt-2 -mr-2 text-secondary hover:text-heading text-xl leading-none z-10"
          aria-label="Close">&times;</button>

  <div class="text-center pt-1 mb-2">
    <h3 class="text-heading font-bold text-lg leading-tight">Top Up Wallet</h3>
  </div>
  <p class="text-xs text-secondary mb-4 text-center">
    Entry tokens:
    <span class="font-mono font-semibold text-heading"
          x-text="($store.session.tokensAvailable | 0)"></span>
  </p>

  <%# PRIMARY CTA — Buy Entry Tokens. Opens the existing pack picker (the auth
      wizard's tokens-picker step) with the exact props showTokensPanel uses.
      swap() (not open) because we're already inside the host, and tokens-picker
      lives on a different modal id (auth). border-primary (always, not just on
      hover) marks this as the primary action. %>
  <button type="button" data-topup-rail="tokens"
          @click="$store.modals.swap('auth', { step: 'tokens-picker', mintedCount: 0, mintedBalance: 0, errorText: '', redirectUrl: '', txSignature: '' })"
          class="w-full flex items-center gap-4 p-4 rounded-xl border-2 border-primary bg-inset hover:bg-surface transition text-left">
    <span class="shrink-0 w-10 h-10 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center text-xl bg-primary">&#127915;</span>
    <span class="flex-1 min-w-0">
      <span class="block text-heading font-semibold text-sm">Buy Entry Tokens</span>
      <span class="block text-xs text-secondary">1 token = 1 contest entry</span>
    </span>
    <svg class="shrink-0 w-4 h-4 text-primary" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
      <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M8.25 4.5l7.5 7.5-7.5 7.5"/>
    </svg>
  </button>

  <%# Quiet link to the Add Funds hub — the USDC fallback. The hub carries the
      Coinbase (Buy USDC) rail plus PayPal / Venmo. returnModal: 'wallet-topup'
      tells the hub's Back link to slide the buyer back HERE rather than to the
      tokens picker. %>
  <button type="button"
          @click="$store.modals.swap('onramp-hub', { returnModal: 'wallet-topup' })"
          class="block mx-auto mt-4 text-sm text-secondary hover:text-heading transition">
    More ways to add funds &rarr;
  </button>
</div>
